57.8	Xerox_Star	Xerox Star	The Star workstation, officially known as the Xerox 8010 Information System, was introduced by Xerox Corporation in 1981. It was the first commercial system to incorporate various technologies that today have become commonplace in personal computers, including a bitmapped display, a window-based graphical user interface, icons, folders, mouse, Ethernet networking, file servers, print servers and e-mail.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/09/Xerox_Star_8010.jpg/250px-Xerox_Star_8010.jpg
